data.title: Pedder Street and the Clock Tower, viewed from the wharf, Hong Kong
data.text:
Notes

University of Bristol - Historical Photographs of China reference number: NA18-04. On the left: Dent & Co offices. In the centre: Clock Tower. The hotel is near the Clock Tower. On the right: Jardine House, headquarters of Jardine Matheson & Co. See NA18-05 and NA18-08. Image from the album 'PHOTOGRAPHS TO ILLUSTRATE MY REPORT DATED 27TH JULY 1889 / S. Brown / Surveyor General' accompanying a report entitled 'PUBLIC WORKS' DEPARTMENT - Report on great storm of 29th and 30th May, 1889'. (National Archives ref: HONG KONG 5. CO 1069/448).
